% ====================================================================
% test_bestagon_proto_fog_perf.trx -- run examples/bestagon-proto/
% proto-fog-perf.trx via the tests/ harness.
% ====================================================================
%
% Thin wrapper: loads proto-fog-perf.trx (Phase 0.6E: fog-of-war perf-
% budget validation per GDD section 11.1), which benches 1000
% compute-fog invocations per variant (naive-bool / bbox-bool / bbox-set)
% on Standard 50x36 and Epic 75x54 fixtures and writes the verdict to
% examples/bestagon-proto/out/fog-perf.md.
%
% Correctness invariants asserted inside the proto (test fails on
% mismatch):
%   - naive-bool produces byte-identical Array<Byte> as bbox-bool
%   - bbox-set length equals bbox-bool popcount
%
% Wall-clock budget verdict (PASS / FAIL on locked decision 32-D
% no-cache stance) is logged to the verdict file but NOT asserted in
% this test -- absolute wall-clock varies by build and host.  The
% proto's stdout summary table is the primary artifact.
%
% Runs on default 1 MB VM via per-iteration save/restore brackets.
% Iteration counts are 20 for naive (already shown hopeless at any N)
% and 200 for bbox + set.  On debug build: ~5-7 minutes.  On prod build
% (./trix.opt): ~20-30 s.
% ====================================================================

(examples/bestagon-proto/proto-fog-perf.trx) run
(__test_ok__) =
